Ability: Serene Grace
EVs: 252 HP / 160 Atk / 96 Spe
Jolly Nature
- Substitute
- Body Slam
- Iron Head
- Stealth Rock/Fire Punch

i like this spread (tho i think its an older one) because normally, dragmag has a very slow jirachi that doesnt do much damage, if any, so having this as a lure showing sub, and then paraflinching the team down for a latios/reun late game sweep is a sight to behold. even without the lure this set can p much 1v1 any non steel types (which magnezone beats steels) and if you went with fire punch instead of stealth rock, playing around this is tough. ive 1v1d gliscor with this.

Turbot (Garchomp) @ Salac Berry / Lum Berry (only if not sub)
Ability: Rough Skin
EVs: 4 HP / 252 Atk / 252 Spe
Jolly Nature
- Substitute / Stealth Rock / Fire Blast
- Swords Dance
- Outrage
- Earthquake

this team is about surprise. so why not surprise salac chomp? chomp is here for the steels that zone dont beat and also a makeshift volcarona check alongside mence. and late game subsalac chomp have gotten me 2 wins so far since its unexpected or unreasonable to predict coming, if thats not to your taste u can always make it rocks for the fpunch rachi or fire blast for skarms.

Ability: Magic Guard
EVs: 192 HP / 64 Def / 252 SpA
Quiet Nature
IVs: 0 Spe
- Trick Room
- Psychic
- Focus Blast
- Shadow Ball

all of the dragons left in ou that i like to use are very weak to rocks, and mamoswine doesnt seem to be the greatest here. since i want to keep this team not weak to hazard i decide to go for reun, and since the team is rather slow anyways for a dragmag this is a good late game sweeper. not much to explain. reun trick rooms. reun kills. thats it.

Other Options:
Keldeo, Heatran, Volcarona and Terrakion are other options i explored over magnezone since the beat volcarona and steels which are things this team appreciate, so if u dont like zone, those 4 are good.
